displayName: Internet Explorer block outdated Active X controls
description:
This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer blocks specific outdated ActiveX controls. Outdated ActiveX controls are never blocked in the Intranet Zone.

If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer blocks outdated ActiveX controls.

If you disable or don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not block specific outdated ActiveX controls.

For more information, see "Outdated ActiveX Controls" in the Internet Explorer TechNet library.
